import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

# Load data
data = pd.read_json('weather.json')

# Plot histogram of temperature
sns.histplot(data=data, x='temperature', kde=True, color='blue')
plt.axvline(data['temperature'].mean(), color='red', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label='Mean')
plt.legend()
plt.title('What is the distribution of temperature in the dataset?')
plt.xlabel('Temperature')
plt.ylabel('Frequency')

# Show plot
plt.show()
```

```
import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

# Load data
data = pd.read_json('weather.json')

# Convert date field to datetime type
data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], format='%Y-%m-%d %H:%M:%S', errors='coerce')

# Drop rows with NaT values
data = data[pd.notna(data['date'])]

# Line chart of humidity over time
sns.lineplot(x='date', y='humidity', data=data)

# Set chart title
plt.title('How does the humidity vary with time?', wrap=True)

# Rotate x-axis labels for legibility
plt.xticks(rotation=45)

# Show plot
plt.show()
```

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

# Load data
data = pd.read_json('weather.json')

# Plot histogram of pressure
sns.histplot(data=data, x='pressure', kde=True, color='blue')
plt.axvline(data['pressure'].mean(), color='red', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label='Mean')
plt.axvline(data['pressure'].median(), color='green', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label='Median')
plt.legend()
plt.title('What is the distribution of pressure in the dataset?')
plt.xlabel('Pressure')
plt.ylabel('Frequency')

plt.show()
```

```
import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import json

with open('weather.json') as f:
    data = pd.json_normalize(json.load(f))

data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], format='%Y-%m-%d')
data = data.dropna(subset=['precipitation'])

fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(10, 6))
sns.scatterplot(x='longitude', y='latitude', hue='precipitation', data=data, ax=ax, palette='coolwarm')
ax.set_xlabel('Longitude')
ax.set_ylabel('Latitude')
ax.set_title('How does the precipitation vary with location?')
plt.show()
```
